.TH SINGINE-AI 1 "2026-03-15" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine\-ai \- AI provider passthrough and governance layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine ai
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIPROVIDER\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai claude
[\fB--model\fR \fIMODEL\fR] [\fB--session\fR \fIID\fR] [\fB--mandate\fR \fIFILE\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai collibra
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai openai
[\fB--model\fR \fIMODEL\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai session
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai mandate
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai flush
[\fB--session\fR \fIID\fR] [\fB--commit\fR]
.PP
.B singine ai status
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B singine ai
is the governance passthrough for AI providers.
Every interaction is mediated by the singine governance layer:
commands are recorded, permissions are checked and logged,
and sessions are serialised to git-managed EDN files for audit.
.PP
No provider is called directly.
All calls go through an
.I AiSession
which enforces the permission model and records every command and outcome.
.SS Provider back-ends
.TP
.B claude
Anthropic Claude (claude-sonnet-4-6, claude-opus-4-6, claude-haiku-4-5).
.TP
.B collibra
Collibra Data Governance Center.
Acts as both a provider (catalog queries) and a mandate grantor.
.TP
.B openai
OpenAI (GPT-4o, o3, Codex passthrough).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B session list
List all recorded sessions in
.IR singine/ai/sessions/ .
.TP
.B session show \fIID\fR
Print the manifest, commands, and permissions for a session.
.TP
.B session export \fIID\fR [\fB--xml\fR|\fB--edn\fR|\fB--json\fR]
Export a session in the requested format.
.TP
.B mandate import [\fB--from\fR \fIPROVIDER\fR]
Import a mandate from a provider (Collibra) and store it in
.IR singine/ai/mandates/ .
.TP
.B mandate list
List all stored mandates.
.TP
.B mandate show \fIID\fR
Print a mandate's permissions and status.
.TP
.B flush [\fB--session\fR \fIID\fR] [\fB--commit\fR]
Flush the current (or named) session's EDN files to disk.
With
.B --commit
also stages and commits them to git.
.TP
.B status
Check connectivity and configuration for all enabled providers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --model \fIMODEL\fR
Override the default model for the provider.
.TP
.B --session \fIID\fR
Attach to or continue an existing session rather than starting a new one.
.TP
.B --mandate \fIFILE\fR
Apply a pre-loaded mandate from an EDN file.
.TP
.B --commit
When used with
.BR flush ,
automatically git-add and git-commit the session files.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Provider configurations live in
.IR singine/ai/config/ :
.PP
.nf
providers.edn   — provider registry
claude.edn      — Anthropic Claude config + default permissions
collibra.edn    — Collibra config + mandate settings
openai.edn      — OpenAI/Codex config
.fi
.PP
Credentials are NOT stored in config files.
Use
.B :credential/source
references:
.nf
"env:ANTHROPIC_API_KEY"
"file:~/.singine/auth/collibra.json"
.fi
.SH SESSION DIRECTORY LAYOUT
.nf
singine/ai/sessions/{session-id}/
  manifest.edn     — session metadata and outcome
  commands.edn     — ordered list of all commands
  permissions.edn  — granted and denied permissions
  outcomes.edn     — produced outcomes with taxonomy refs
.fi
.SH MANDATE DELEGATION
Collibra can issue mandates that pre-authorise a scope of actions for
the singine agent.  The delegation workflow is:
.PP
.nf
1. Create a "Governance Policy" asset in Collibra
2. singine ai mandate import --from collibra
3. Review and git-commit: singine ai flush --commit
4. Reference the mandate: singine ai claude --mandate collibra-{date}.edn
.fi
.SH PERMISSION MODEL
Permissions are ODRL-aligned:
.B action
(read/write/commit/execute/api-call/delegate),
.B resource
(file path, URL, git ref, Collibra asset ID),
.B decision
(granted/denied/conditional).
.PP
Permissions granted in a session are flushed to:
.I singine/ai/sessions/{session-id}/permissions.edn
.PP
All-session grants are accumulated in:
.I singine/ai/permissions/granted.edn
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-decide (1),
.BR singine-activity (1),
.BR singine-model (1)
